==Irish==
===Etymology===
From French [[Noël]], itself a derivation of Latin [[natalis]], referring to the birth of Christ.
===Noun===
'''Nollaig''', ''fem.'', ''5th decl.'',  no plural
# [[December]]
# [[Christmas Day]], the 25th of December.
# the [[season]] surrounding Christmas Day
#: "[[beannacht|Beannachtaí]] na Nollaig"